channel.title: Would anyone like to help me get the Null's Object ID List? I already started
channel.description:
Hello. I have wanted to make a house, actually, a mansion!!! Okay. Back to the point. I want to put together a team to help me make a list of null IDs. For example, I made a list of 83-205. I dont NEED help, but it'll take ages before I finish. I already one helper, and hasnt done much yet :P. I also wanna help people by releasing this to help All people. What I mean by this is like this.
[b]97 = Beginning / End of a stair case[/b]
So far, I have this done. It took me about an hour to do, but the null IDs go up to 9999...
[code]Null Object ID List Made By: Lin Numbers 83 - 205 R = ReplaceGlobalObject A/M = Add / MakeGlobalObject N/A = Niether F = ReplaceFloor U = Unknown
83 = Nothing = N/A 84 = Nothing = N/A 85 = Something Invisible = A/M 88 = Something Invisible = A/M 97 = Beginning / End of a stair case it looks like... = A/M 107 = Black square with what looks like the corner of a rug.. Almost like a kite... = F 108 = Black Rectangle = F 109 = Black Square = F 110 = A strange shaped brown thing... Almost shaped like a Manta Ray = F 111 = Brown/Black Arrow SE = F 112 = Brown/Black Arrow NW = F 113 = Brown/Black Arrow SW = F 137 = Gate Door with lock = A/M 138 = Gate Door with lock = A/M 139 = Gate Door with lock = A/M 140 = Gate Door with lock = A/M 141 = Gate Door with lock = A/M 142 = Gate Door with lock = A/M 143 = Gate Door with lock = A/M 144 = Gate Door with lock = A/M 145 = Gate Door with lock = A/M 146 = Invisible Wall W = A/M 147 = Invisible Wall W = A/M 148 = Invisible Wall W = A/M 149 = Invisible Corner S & W = A/M 150 = Invisible Corner S & W = A/M 151 = Invisible Corner S & W = A/M 161 = Invisible Corner S & W = A/M 168 = Short Wooden Gate = R 169 = Like... A floor thing... Like this: |=| Except with bigger = and more of them = F 174 = Litter... With a yellow piece and grey things... = F 175 = Litter... With 2 bottles and grey things... = F 176 = A bunch of brown triangles, small ones = F 177 = 4 Brown small triangles = F 178 = 5 Brown small triangles = F 179 = A bunch of grey triangles, small ones = F 180 = A lot more grey triangles, small ones = F 181 = 4 Grey small triangles = F 182 = 3 Grey small triangles = F 183 = Nothing 184 = A bunch of diamond/triangle brown things = F 185 = Normal Wall 186 = 5 Brown things; circles, diamonds, and triangles = F 191 = Left Half of a Big Door (cant open) with a green star on it = A/M 192 = Right Half of a Big Door (cant open) with a green star on it = A/M 193 = Part of a short wooden fence = R 196 = Weather Changer? Time Changer? Time Teller? Invisible/Non-Blocker = U 197 = Weather Changer? Time Changer? Time Teller? Invisible/Non-Blocker = U 198 = Weather Changer? Time Changer? Time Teller? Invisible/Non-Blocker = U 199 = REALLY strange wall... Almost looks like a sand wall... Has a ledge coming out of it... = A/M 205 = Left half of a big door it looks like... Almost like 191 but no ropes/fence and a different green symbol.[/code] Where it says Made By Lin will change and other people's names will go there.
In order to help me, post here or PM me. You must have done [b]Federexer's Adding Global Objects[/b] and [b]Federexer's Buildings[/b]. This is an example of finding out whether it is a ReplaceObject, Replacefloor, or Add/MakeGlobalObject.
[code]ReplaceObject(3226, 3429, 205, 0);// makeGlobalObject(3226, 3428, 205, 0, 10);// Replacefloor(3226, 3427, 205, 0); [/code] This is making it so like if the item spawns on the coords 3226, 3429 itll be a ReplaceObject required. And you should get the rest. When you have a list of atleast a 100, PM me and I will add it to my list at my site.
Hope you will help!!!
~Lin
